<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Are Cobbers still made by Allen's?</h3>
<p>Yes, Cobbers are still produced and are genuine <a href="https://sweetsworld.com.au/where-to-buy/allens-lollies-australia/">Allen's products, just like the ones you remember from the old corner shop days</a>. They maintain the same delicious chewy caramel and chocolate coating that made them an Australian favourite.</p>

<h3>Why do Cobbers stick to your teeth?</h3>
<p>Cobbers are made with chewy caramel that's quite sticky by nature, which is part of their charm as a traditional hard caramel lolly. This stickiness is why many customers jokingly mention they can remove fillings – it's all part of the authentic Cobbers experience!</p>

<h3>How much product do I get in a display box of Cobbers?</h3>
<p>A display box of Cobbers contains 1.8kg of the chewy caramel chocolate-coated lollies, making it perfect for stocking up or sharing with family and friends. If you're looking to buy in larger quantities, you can find a full range of <a href="https://sweetsworld.com.au/where-to-buy/bulk-lollies-australia/">bulk lollies in Australia</a> for parties and events.</p>


