<h3>What's the difference between Cobbers and other caramel chocolates?</h3>
<p>Cobbers are specifically chewy caramel wrapped in milk chocolate, setting them apart from harder caramel lollies. Their unique texture and the way they interact with your teeth is what makes them such a nostalgic and distinctive Australian treat. For those interested in exploring other chocolate options, we have <a href="https://sweetsworld.com.au/where-to-buy/cadbury-favourites-australia/">Cadbury Favourites</a> and other <a href="https://sweetsworld.com.au/where-to-buy/belgian-chocolate-australia/">authentic Belgian chocolate available online</a>.</p>

<h3>Are Cobbers suitable for kids?</h3>
<p>While Cobbers are loved by Australians of all ages, they're best suited for older children and adults due to their sticky nature and the potential to affect dental fillings. Always supervise younger children when enjoying these chewy treats. For age-appropriate alternatives, check out our guide to the <a href="https://sweetsworld.com.au/candy-guides/best-candy-for-kids-australia/">best candy for kids in Australia</a>.</p>

